1. Roadmap:

This is the first part of the creation process, serving as the blueprint for the entire learning journey and the core structure upon which the course will be built.

Once the app understands all the requirements of the user, a personalized roadmap will be created that focuses on both academic accuracy and customization.

The process will involve extensive research, utilizing the internet, books, and documents to compile a detailed syllabus that outlines the subject matter comprehensively. This will be organized from section to section, chapter to chapter, and point to point, covering everything from basic concepts to advanced expertise in a step-by-step manner. Each chapter and the key points within will be clearly marked.

Additionally, practice problem sets will be incorporated into the roadmap after every chapter or set of chapters, based on the user’s requirements. This roadmap will not simply serve as an index of a book but a book itself; it will function as a complete learning resource, containing all necessary details for the next phase, “Organizing the Data.”

Projects will also be developed after specific segments of the course are completed. These projects will start with basic concepts and become progressively more complex if user approval is given at the understanding stage.  These projects will help user understand and judge their own learning and get an idea of what they are for now.

This is how the roadmap/ HANDBOOK looks:

