1. Organizing the data :

Now that the roadmap is ready and the AI understands the process, it begins by searching YouTube. Following the specified process, the AI filters videos based on their titles and thumbnails, selecting those that match the specific chapter or point.

Suppose a C++ learning roadmap has been created. The AI will first examine Chapter One: Variables. It will go to YouTube to find all the videos on C++ variables and select the ones that match the topic. The AI will then filter these videos by evaluating their views, likes, comments, and the number of subscribers of the creators.

If practically possible, the AI will watch the entire video and check the timestamps to verify whether the content covers all the required topics on variables. If the video meets the criteria, it will be shortlisted and added to Chapter One of the course. If not, the AI will continue watching other videos, repeating the process until a suitable video is found or a list of good videos is compiled.

*THE PROCESS.

    (PHASE 1: READ )

AI will read and understand the entire handbook to know what to find on YouTube. First, it will review Unit 1 and Chapter 1: Variables and understand the content within it.
|
(PHASE 2: RESEARCH )
Step 1:* Initially, the AI will search for resources related to the topic of the roadmap or handbook. It will look for any videos, playlists, or courses that cover the entire handbook or the majority of its units and chapters. If such resources are found, they will be sent to Phase 3 for verification of their coverage. If no comprehensive video, playlist, or course is found, proceed to Step 2.

Step 2: If resources for the entire handbook are not found, the AI will search for videos, playlists, or courses specifically related to the first unit, starting with Unit 1. If resources for Unit 1 are found, they will be sent to Phase 3. If not, the AI will then look for resources related to the chapters within Unit 1. The core idea is to follow a step-by-step process: if the search for the entire handbook fails, focus on the units, starting with the first unit. The AI will not move on to the next unit until it has fully satisfied the content requirements for the first unit.

Step 3: The AI will search YouTube for videos related to the specific chapters within Unit 1.

If a video for the handbook, specifically for the first unit and first chapter, cannot be found, the user will be asked if they prefer any free or paid courses on the specific topic (if there are no videos available on YouTube). The next steps will be determined based on the user’s preference, but this will only happen if the videos are not available on YouTube, which is uncommon.
|
(PHASE 3: SELECTION )
Select the top videos based on views, likes, comments, and subscribers. Through this verification process, the top few videos will be selected.
|
(PHASE 4: VERIFICATION)
[The AI will watch and analyze videos one by one to determine whether each video contains the required content. If a video meets all the necessary criteria, it will be shortlisted. If it does not meet the criteria, the AI will move on to the next video and repeat the process. This will continue until a suitable video is found. ]

