CASE 3: What if 2, 3, or 4 videos on the same topic are very similar? There are hundreds of videos covering one subject. After filtering, if multiple videos are shortlisted and contain similar content, all of these videos will be displayed for the user. The user can then select which one they want to watch, since they are nearly identical.

However, the filtering process will still rely on factors like views, subscribers, likes, comments, and the content covered. Consequently, no more than four videos will typically be at the same level of relevance.

