1. Tracking The Process :

Once the Handbook is ready and the entire course is filled with videos, the user will begin consuming the content. The app will track the user’s progress, including the percentage of the course completed and the number of days the user has watched videos. Consistent days of watching will be marked similarly to Snapchat streaks.

Users will receive a tag based on their level in the course, determined by their completion percentage:

* 10% = Beginner
* 50% = Pro
* 80% = Skilled
* 90% = Master

The tag will advance after completing projects following specific units. For example, if units 2, 3, and 4 are completed, a project will be assigned. If the project is completed correctly, the user will progress from Beginner to Pro.

Throughout the course, there will be tests and projects, with all marks recorded and saved in the user’s profile.

